# WTF Platform — Core Rules

**Canonical source:** Read `claude.md` (or `CLAUDE.md`) at session start for full role, git workflow, linting, and `/start-dev-flow` lifecycle.

## Session start (every conversation)

1. Read `MEMORY.md`, `ERRORS.md`, and `BACKLOG.md` before coding.
2. Follow branch rules: never touch `main`; feature branches `feat/<app>/<name>` from `guru` / `trainer` / `node-server`.

## Communication

- No filler openings. Match answer length to question complexity.
- Ask before assuming. Offer 2–3 options before significant work; wait for choice.
- After any coding task, end with: **Files changed** / **What was modified** / **Files intentionally not touched** / **Follow-up needed**.

## Code boundaries

- Strict scope: only change what the task requires.
- Stop for confirmation before large logic rewrites or destructive actions.
- `flutter analyze` / `npm run lint` must pass before commits.

## Skills (project)

| Skill | When |
|-------|------|
| `grill-me` | Stress-test a plan or design |
| `start-dev-flow` | User sends `/start-dev-flow` |
| `record-activity` | After completed work or when updating project docs |
